    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Puzzling Medicare Plan</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Martha B Weisberg letter holds that she is puzzled, not just by complexity of Medicare drug plan, but also by how it was passed by Democrats and Republicans</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''73 Options for Medicare Plan Fuel Chaos, Not Prescriptions'' (front page, May 12): In addition to being outraged by the Medicare plan, I am completely puzzled, not just by the apparent complexity of the plan, but also by how it was passed by both Democrats and Republicans. Even AARP endorsed it, acknowledging that it wasn't perfect.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''73 Options for Medicare Plan Fuel Chaos, Not Prescriptions'' (front page, May 12): In addition to being outraged by the Medicare plan, I am completely puzzled, not just by the apparent complexity of the plan, but also by how it was passed by both Democrats and Republicans. Even AARP endorsed it, acknowledging that it wasn't perfect.</p>
        <p>I suggest that each of you who voted in favor of it sit down with your 70-year-old loved one and ask him or her to explain this imperfect plan to you.</p>
        <p>MARTHA B. WEISBERG  Bergenfield, N.J., May 13, 2004</p>
      </block>
